This repository's contents under `worker/` are derived from the
Cloudflare Worker in cardputer-claude-os. The upstream code was
imported verbatim and then modified as follows:

  - The `/ask` handler's speech-to-text step has been switched from
    OpenAI's hosted Whisper API to Cloudflare Workers AI's
    `@cf/openai/whisper` model (via an `[ai]` binding in
    `wrangler.toml`). This removes the `OPENAI_API_KEY` dependency.
    Notice of modification per Apache 2.0 §4(b) appears at the top of
    `worker/src/worker.js` and in `worker/README.md`.

All other contents under `worker/` (auth flow, conversation-memory
logic, wire format, deploy steps, package.json) remain as written
upstream; credit goes to its upstream authors.

The contents of `device/` are an original port of the Push-to-Claude
device application from MicroPython on the M5Stack Cardputer to
C++/Arduino on the M5Stack Core2, using the M5Unified library. The
port preserves the on-device protocol (raw WAV body to /ask, JSON
prompt to /ask-text, x-device-secret auth header) so the upstream
Worker continues to work with this device.
